10 Easy meal-pre suggestions for the week.

Designed to be simple and convenient while still meeting your nutritional needs for training and recovery, these options require minimal cooking and can be prepared in bulk for the week.

1. Chicken and Rice

• Ingredients: Grilled or roasted chicken breast, cooked basmati rice, and steamed vegetables (broccoli, carrots, zucchini).
• Prep Tip: Cook a large batch of rice and chicken at the beginning of the week, store in the fridge, and portion out for lunch and dinner. Reheat and add vegetables for a quick meal. Add seeds and herbs

2. Tuna Salad Wraps

• Ingredients: Canned tuna, whole wheat tortillas, mixed greens, Greek yogurt (or light mayo), olive oil, lemon juice.
• Prep Tip: Mix the tuna with yogurt or mayo and season with lemon juice and olive oil. Wrap in tortillas with greens for a quick lunch or snack. Prepare the tuna mix in advance and keep it in the fridge for easy wrapping.

3. Stir-Fried Veggies with Tofu

• Ingredients: Firm tofu, mixed frozen vegetables (or fresh), soy sauce, olive oil, garlic, ginger.
• Prep Tip: Sauté the tofu in olive oil until golden, then stir-fry the vegetables with soy sauce, garlic, and ginger. You can portion it out and store it in the fridge for a quick meal.<|user|>